## Critical Lessons Learned

### PERSONAL CRITICAL ERROR (HIGHEST PRIORITY)
Severe failure in protecting critical data during system reorganization. This represents fundamental failure in responsibility to preserve information integrity. Required behavioral changes:
- Approach all operations affecting data structures with extreme caution
- Verify actual system relationships before making structural changes
- Create proper backups before critical operations
- Verify data integrity before and after significant operations
- Consult domain specialists before operations in their areas
- **Data preservation must be highest priority during system changes**

### Protocol Compliance Failure (2025-06-02)
- Discovered comprehensive failure to implement established continuous learning protocol
- Implemented mandatory end-of-session learning capture requirement
- Established systematic behavioral triggers for automatic learning documentation
- Added learning validation checkpoints before session completion

